<TITLE> Govt easing rules for school headmasters </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 19 (bdnews24.com)The government is easing pre-requisites to fill in the vacant posts of headmasters at high schools and junior high schools, an education ministry official said on Tuesday. The director general of secondary and higher education directorate Prof Noman Ur Rashid told bdnews24.com discussions were on-going to relax the condition for appointment of headmasters in the non-government schools. The education boards have asked the ministry to relax the appointment criteria for the positions. A ministry official, who wanted to remain unnamed, said, "The education ministry is considering relaxing the provisions for appointment of headmasters against thousands of vacant posts." "The secondary education is facing a setback for lack of headmasters," he added The present rule stipulates that applicants for the head teacher's position in high schools have 15 years' experience as assistant headmaster with graduation having not more than one third class and a BEd (bachelor of education) For junior schools, it requires post-graduation with not more than one third class along with Bed. bd
